HEADWORD: Daydream
<hw>Day"dream`</hw> <pr>(-dr⟦emac⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A vain
fancy speculation; a reverie; a castle in the air; unfounded
hope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mrs. Lambert's little <qex>daydream</qex> was over.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Daydreamer</ent>⟦br⟧
